author: pburba
msg: Follow-up to r28979, if we ask the repos for the mergeinfo of a non-existent
URL@rev we now get an error, not an empty mergeinfo hash.
* subversion/libsvn_client/mergeinfo.h
(svn_client__get_repos_mergeinfo): Describe new behavior that came about
when the reintegrate branch was merged to trunk.

author: pburba
msg: Follow-up to r28979, eliminate Win32 C4715 warning, not all control paths
return a value.
* subversion/libsvn_client/merge.c
(calculate_left_hand_side): Return SVN_NO_ERROR at end.  There really isn't
a problem, since all control paths return an error or abort, just trying
to cut down on the noise.
